channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: June 10, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The UN Security Council adopted a resolution proposed by the United States for a permanent ceasefire and release of the hostages in Gaza.

item.title: Russia, Belarus launch drills to train troops in tactical nuclear weapons
item.description: Russia and its ally Belarus have launched a second stage of drills intended to train their troops in tactical nuclear weapons, part of the Kremlin’s efforts to discourage the West from ramping up support for Ukraine

item.title: Malawi's vice president killed in plane crash along with 9 others
item.description: Vice President of Malawi Dr. Saulos Chilima and his wife were killed when their military plane crashed on the way to a funeral, the government says.

item.title: Apple introduces AI to its products at WWDC
item.description: Apple introduced "Apple Intelligence" -- a suite of artificial intelligence tools -- to its products at its annual Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC) on Monday, while announcing a host of Apple product updates.

item.title: Frank Carroll, figure skating coach behind Michelle Kwan, Evan Lysacek, dies at 85
item.description: Longtime figure skating coach Frank Carroll, who over the course of a 60-year career helped guide six Olympic medalists at 10 Winter Games, including Michelle Kwan and Evan Lysacek, has died

item.title: Prosecutors' star witness faces cross-examination in Bob Menendez trial
item.description: Jose Uribe, an insurance broker who is the prosecution's star witness, has detailed how he says he bribed Sen. Bob Menendez and his wife.

item.title: Jury begins deliberations in Hunter Biden's federal gun trial
item.description: Jury deliberations began Monday and will resume tomorrow in Hunter Biden's federal gun trial in Delaware.

item.title: Soldiers, police search for missing plane carrying Malawi vice president
item.description: Soldiers, police officers and forest rangers are continuing to search for a missing military plane carrying Malawi’s vice president, a former first lady and eight others that is suspected to have crashed in a mountainous region in the north of the country
